copyBlock.cwc:
Is vodka gluten-free?

Vodka is generally a gluten-free alcoholic beverage. The only time vodka isn't gluten-free is when it is a specific flavor that requires gluten ingredients.

Can vodka be kept in the fridge or freezer?

If you prefer your vodka to be chilled, you can keep it in either the fridge or the freezer. Due to its high ethanol content, vodka will never fully freeze, but it will get cold. Keeping vodka at a controlled, cold temperature can bring out its flavors and allow it to be stronger in taste.

How long can a bottle of vodka stay good after opening?

Depending on the brand of vodka, it can stay good for 10 to 20 years. Vodka typically doesn't go bad, though it will taste better the sooner it is consumed after opening the seal on the bottle.
